					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Records the Vana-nāyaka (the lord of the jungle) who is known as Pōndai-nātha who is Aja (who is not born), who was worshipped by <hi rend="italic">Agṉi</hi> at first, who was worshipped by the dēvās in <hi rend="italic">Trēta-yuga</hi> and by saints like Rēvasa in <hi rend="italic">Dvāpāra-yuga,</hi> has been installed here in <hi rend="italic">Kaliyuga.</hi> The deity is smeared with sandal paste.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
